{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Making the UK education curriculum more inclusive of BAME history",
        "additional_details": "Recent events in the US has sparked conversation amongst young people regarding the extent the current curriculum educates students on concepts such as institutional racism, White supremacy and celebration of BAME history and cultures. \r\nRacism stems from a lack of education and it is the responsibility of the Government to ensure that the students are receiving a holistic education from the top-down.",
        "background": "Rewrite the education curriculum to be more inclusive of BAME history - making topics on the historical and current impacts of European colonisation, institutional racism and slavery on BAME societies compulsory for all UK students to learn. As well, as celebration of BAME history and cultures.",
